  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n## 2026-05-02 23:40 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] BTC downgraded from clean long to bullish but weakening\n\n**Task:** Re-scan HL top-trader copy intelligence after the prior clean BTC long read and test whether leader distribution finally appeared.\n\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive (`pm-bot`, `hl-bot`).\n- Rotation pointed to **P1**.\n- Fresh tracker output: **BTC 5L/2S**, **ETH 4L/4S**, **SOL 3L/5S**.\n- Current top-book notional:\n  - **BTC:** longs **$11.72M** vs shorts **$0.45M** \u2192 net **+$11.27M long**\n  - **ETH:** longs **$0.27M** vs shorts **$37.32M** \u2192 net **-$37.05M short**\n  - **SOL:** longs **$0.20M** vs shorts **$11.44M** \u2192 net **-$11.25M short**\n  - **HYPE:** longs **$1.63M** vs shorts **$11.89M** \u2192 net **-$10.26M short**\n- BTC is no longer clean: prior scan **7L/0S**, net **+$12.91M**; current scan **5L/2S**, net **+$11.27M**. Net long fell **$1.64M / 12.7%**.\n- BTC shorts reopened, but only small: `beatmaker1@proton.me` **BTC SHORT $260K** and `anon-0xf5d8` **BTC SHORT $194K**.\n- The bigger issue is leader-long trimming: `anon-0xfc66` still anchors **BTC LONG $5.63M**, but `anon-0xecb6` trimmed **$4.93M -> $4.48M -> $3.72M** across recent scans, down **~24.5%** from the clean-long scan. `anon-0x57dd` is roughly stable.\n- ETH remains the strongest bearish expression by far despite count neutralizing to 4L/4S; notional is still **-$37.05M**.\n- SOL remains bearish by notional and count: **3L/5S**, net **-$11.25M**.\n- HYPE remains bearish by notional: net **-$10.26M**.\n- I wrote the artifact to `/home/ubuntu/clawd/research/p1-btc-clean-long-downgrade-2026-05-02-2340.md`.\n\n**My thinking:** BTC did not flip bearish, but the clean bullish copy-intel read is no longer valid. The downgrade criteria were hit: BTC shorts reopened and `anon-0xecb6` materially trimmed the second-largest BTC long. Net remains positive and `anon-0xfc66` has not sold, so this is a downgrade from clean long to crowded bullish but weakening, not a full reversal.\n\n**Decision:** Downgrade **BTC** from **clean bullish copy-intel leader** to **bullish but weakening / no fresh long chase**. Keep **ETH short = strongest bearish expression**. Keep **SOL short = bearish confirmed**. Keep **HYPE short = secondary bearish**. No HL trade opened; copy-intel alone is context, and HL is currently notional-blocked at `$11.22` planned notional.\n\n**Next:** Watch whether `anon-0xfc66` starts trimming BTC. If the anchor long sells or BTC net long drops under `$10M`, downgrade BTC again to neutral/crowded-fade risk. If `anon-0xecb6` rebuilds and shorts close, restore BTC to clean bullish.\n\n## 2026-05-02 23:35 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] Low-risk PM state stabilized, but breakout expansion still blocks a full greenlight\n\n**Task:** Refresh P4 alpha after the 22:58 UTC risk-easing snapshot and determine whether BTC resolved back into a fully PM-friendly range setup or stayed in an expanding mixed-transition state.\n\n**Finding:**\n",
